<div class="page" id="page-timeline">
  <h2>Engineering Timeline</h2>
  <p>Each step built on the last. The progression from REST APIs to AI systems to cloud deployment to DevSecOps is deliberate — each project introduced a constraint the next one had to solve.</p>
  <div style="height:32px"></div>
  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="tl-entry"><div class="tl-dot done"></div>
      <div class="tl-meta"><span class="tl-period">Nov 2025</span><span class="tl-title">Backend APIs &amp; AI Automation Internship</span></div>
      <div class="tl-body">Joined The Entrepreneurship Network as an AI Intern. Built FastAPI backends, integrated LLM APIs, contributed to workflow automation using n8n. First production exposure to AI-powered systems running against real business use cases.</div>
      <div class="chips"><span class="chip">FastAPI</span><span class="chip">LLM APIs</span><span class="chip">n8n</span><span class="chip">Python</span><span class="chip">REST APIs</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-entry"><div class="tl-dot done"></div>
      <div class="tl-meta"><span class="tl-period">Dec 2025</span><span class="tl-title">AI Fake News Detection — Prompt-as-Contract Design</span></div>
      <div class="tl-body">Moved beyond basic LLM calls. Designed an output schema enforced inside the prompt itself — making responses machine-parseable. First systematic application of treating prompt structure as an API contract rather than natural language instruction.</div>
      <div class="chips"><span class="chip">Prompt Engineering</span><span class="chip">Output Schema Design</span><span class="chip">MongoDB</span><span class="chip">Docker</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-entry"><div class="tl-dot done"></div>
      <div class="tl-meta"><span class="tl-period">Jan 2026</span><span class="tl-title">RAG Research Assistant — Retrieval Before Generation</span></div>
      <div class="tl-body">Introduced the retrieval layer: documents chunked, embedded, indexed, then retrieved semantically before LLM inference. Grounded generation in actual document content rather than model memory — measurably reducing hallucination risk.</div>
      <div class="chips"><span class="chip">RAG</span><span class="chip">Vector Search</span><span class="chip">Context Engineering</span><span class="chip">Chunking Strategy</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-entry"><div class="tl-dot done"></div>
      <div class="tl-meta"><span class="tl-period">Jan 2026</span><span class="tl-title">AICTE IoT Cloud Internship — Grade O (Outstanding)</span></div>
      <div class="tl-body">10-week AWS Skill Builder curriculum via EduSkills/AICTE. Covered IoT cloud architecture, device-to-cloud pipelines, and edge computing patterns. Directly reinforced the Cloud &amp; Edge Computing degree specialisation with structured AWS lab work.</div>
      <div class="chips"><span class="chip">AWS IoT</span><span class="chip">Cloud Architecture</span><span class="chip">Edge Computing</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-entry"><div class="tl-dot done"></div>
      <div class="tl-meta"><span class="tl-period">Feb 2026</span><span class="tl-title">Real-Time Booking + DevSecOps Pipeline</span></div>
      <div class="tl-body">Concurrency challenges in the booking system forced atomic database operations and real-time WebSocket sync. The DevSecOps pipeline made vulnerability scanning a blocking CI stage — not a post-deploy alert. Security moved from afterthought to delivery gate.</div>
      <div class="chips"><span class="chip">Socket.IO</span><span class="chip">Concurrency</span><span class="chip">GitHub Actions</span><span class="chip">Docker</span><span class="chip">DevSecOps</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-entry"><div class="tl-dot done"></div>
